  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GH-0000244 Improve Literacy Levels Bolgatanga</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve literacy levels Ghanaian children by providing the school libraries with books for a period of three years and by giving the teachers of the same schools training. One of the libraries will be an example library which can be used for training (library skills) purposes as well

20 schools, 40 teachers, 6566 students.  

1: Poverty reduction (following STAR-school model)
&#x2022;	In 2019, 20 schools have received at least 865 books for the school library. 

&#x2022;	In 2019, the literacy levels of 600 pupils are assessed based on the methodology that the partner chooses to be the best suited to show the impact the project wants to reach (this can be the EGRA methodology or another evaluation method).

2: Capacity building
&#x2022;	In 2019, 40 teachers will have the knowledge they need in order to run the school library successfully and know how to inspire the children to read. 
&#x2022;	The education officer of CESRUD and one member of Biblionef Ghana will be present during the workshop. 
3. Lobby and advocacy
Biblionef together with CESRUD will visit the Regional Education office in Bolgatanga to discuss ways the project can be supported and sustained 
To create visibility for the project, the books will be handed over to the schools at a  handing over ceremony with local authority presence.</narrative>
  </description>
